Let me start this with I hate leaving bad reviews. I try to follow my rule of only reviewing places I love because i know how hard it is to run a business and places can have off days. However this was my 2nd time trying Melt Shop after being disappointed the first time. I never tried this location so I thought maybe it would be better. Unfortunately the grilled cheese was bland and the bread rather hard and chewy, (like I couldn’t even bite through the crust).I don’t know how they cook these but if you ever had a the Starbucks grilled cheese it’s kind of like that. Whether or not they actually grill it, it certainly tastes like it’s pre made and then microwaved. For almost $6 it should be edible and this almost wasn’t. I’ve had better grilled cheese at delis for less money. If you are really a lover of grilled cheese and visiting the city I recommend Noormans Kil in brooklyn. The grilled cheeses are between 7-8 and they use quality cheese! (I’m not in any way affiliated with them I just love grilled cheese and made a point of finding good ones when I moved to nyc). Loaded tots were also a disappointment the cheese sauce doesn’t taste anything like cheese to me, and small portion for the price as well. With all the options nyc has to offer you can find a better bang for your buck elsewhere and leave feeling satisfied.
